  lines:
  - text: "Look ! GOLD and FAITH of the city increased. \r\n"
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "The other two elements are SKILLS and the number of craftsmen present
      in the city. \r\n\nEach choice will have an influence on these parameters.
      Choose wisely.\r\n"
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "There are different types of recruitable characters: \r\nPilgrims, as
      we just saw. "
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "Special pilgrims: they bring the same resources as regular pilgrims but
      they also bring particular objects. Stay alert ! \r\n\nCraftsman: they bring
      SKILLS but cost GOLD to recruit. \n"
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: 'Finally, thieves ! They are disguised as regular pilgrims and once recruited
      they steal GOLD. '
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "Other pilgrims of the city don\u2019t feel safe and will stop less in
      Saint Bertrand. Thus, decreasing FAITH of the city as well. \nBe careful ! 
      \r"
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "The choices will help you complete the objectives of the era you are playing.
      \r\n"
    questionTuto: 0
  - text: "Click on the objectives panel! \r\n"
    questionTuto: 0
